25 | title=Not the Love Boat: Smith on ''Dead Ahead'' | work=Comic Book Resources | date=July 21, 2008}}</ref>\n*''[[Dead Body Road]]''\n* ''[[Dead Space (comics)|Dead Space]]''\n* ''[[Deadly Class]]'' (2013 \u2013 ongoing)\n* ''[[Deadworld]]'' vol. 3 (2005\u20132006; previous volumes from [[Caliber Press]])\n* ''[[Death Dealer (comics)|Death Dealer]]''\n* ''[[Death Jr.]]''\n*''Death or Glory'', by [[Rick Remender]] and [[Bengal (artist)|Bengal]] (2018\u2013)\n* ''[[Deathblow (comics)|Deathblow]]''\n* ''[[Demon Slayer]]'' (1998\u20132000)\n* ''Deep Sleeper'' (2004; first two issues published by Oni Press)\n* ''Defcon 4''\n* ''Defiance''\n* ''[[Deity: Revelations]]''\n* ''Descender'' (2015\u2013)\n* ''[[Desperate Times]]''\n* ''The Detonator'' (2004\u20132005; by Mike Baron)\n* ''[[A Distant Soil]]''\n* ''[[Divine Right: The Adventures of Max Faraday|Divine Right]]''\n* ''[[Doom's IV]]''\n* ''[[Drain (comics)|Drain]]''\n* ''[[Drifter (comics)|Drifter]]'' (2014 \u2013 ongoing)\n* ''The Drowned''<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.readaboutcomics.com/2004/04/26/drowned/ | title=Drowned | work=Read About Comics | date=May 2, 2009}}</ref>\n* ''[[Drums (comics)|Drums]]''\n* ''[[Dust (Image Comics)|Dust]]''<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.12gaugecomics.com/dust.html | work=12 Gauge Comics | title=Paolo Parente's Dust | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081019093910/http://www.12gaugecomics.com/dust.html | archivedate=2008-10-19 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.dustgame.com | title=Paolo Parente\u2019s Dust: The Army Weekly}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/news/newsitem.cgi?id=9533 | title=''Dust'' Debuts From mink and Parente This Summer at Image | date=February 1, 2007 | work=Comic Book Resources}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/news/newsitem.cgi?id=11715 | title=Preview: ''Dust'' #2 | date=August 28, 2007 | work=Comic Book Resources}}</ref>\n* ''Dusty Star''\n* ''[[DV8]]''\n* ''[[Dy